1
00:01:32,759 --> 00:01:36,974
Our wedding anniversary's coming up.
How do you celebrate?

2
00:01:36,974 --> 00:01:41,767
I try to find out what she wants
and we eat out together,

3
00:01:41,767 --> 00:01:45,475
and I also give her a little something.

4
00:01:45,475 --> 00:01:47,767
I hate shopping.

5
00:01:49,266 --> 00:01:54,767
I think your wife would enjoy going
to see some theater or something.

6
00:01:54,767 --> 00:01:57,600
Or contemporary dance.

7
00:01:57,600 --> 00:02:01,767
How can you tell? Wow, she does like those things.

8
00:02:01,767 --> 00:02:03,058
I thought so.

9
00:02:09,974 --> 00:02:10,974
Wait...

10
00:02:14,850 --> 00:02:17,558
Hi, long time no see.

11
00:02:27,891 --> 00:02:34,475
[The Cornered Mouse Dreams of Cheese]

12
00:02:40,576 --> 00:02:42,037
What's this?

13
00:02:42,037 --> 00:02:43,370
Just take a look.

14
00:02:52,965 --> 00:02:55,799
[Investigation Report]

15
00:03:13,730 --> 00:03:14,897
What the hell?

16
00:03:18,814 --> 00:03:20,897
I work here now.

17
00:03:23,980 --> 00:03:25,230
You're a private eye?

18
00:03:26,814 --> 00:03:30,563
I was surprised to find out my target was you.

19
00:03:32,980 --> 00:03:34,064
You want money?

20
00:03:34,064 --> 00:03:36,855
No, I'm a legit investigator.

21
00:03:36,855 --> 00:03:41,605
But since it was you I sort of felt a twinge,

22
00:03:41,605 --> 00:03:43,147
of conscience, if you will.

23
00:03:44,558 --> 00:03:47,230
You mean, you won't tell?

24
00:03:47,230 --> 00:03:49,397
I'm wavering. It's my job.

25
00:03:57,730 --> 00:04:00,522
Could you cover it up somehow?

26
00:04:00,522 --> 00:04:03,563
Thought you'd say that.

27
00:04:03,563 --> 00:04:05,064
You won't tell?

28
00:04:09,271 --> 00:04:10,480
What should I do?

29
00:04:14,939 --> 00:04:17,980
I'd like you to think for yourself.

30
00:04:17,980 --> 00:04:19,147
What?

31
00:04:25,397 --> 00:04:27,064
Then tonight...

32
00:04:30,478 --> 00:04:33,383
I know a good restaurant.

33
00:04:33,383 --> 00:04:35,188
Are you OK with raw fish?

34
00:04:35,188 --> 00:04:36,397
Sushi?

35
00:04:37,688 --> 00:04:38,688
Love it.

36
00:04:39,688 --> 00:04:40,814
Then let's go.

37
00:04:42,897 --> 00:04:44,980
Here you go. Horse mackerel.

38
00:05:01,897 --> 00:05:03,480
Your wife, Chikako.

39
00:05:07,563 --> 00:05:11,397
You had a weakness for her type since university.

40
00:05:11,397 --> 00:05:12,563
You think so?

41
00:05:13,772 --> 00:05:18,563
Pretty, but cunning. A typically feminine type of girl.

42
00:05:21,064 --> 00:05:22,397
Maybe so.

43
00:05:26,106 --> 00:05:28,397
Why did you marry her?

44
00:05:30,188 --> 00:05:31,647
I wonder why.

45
00:05:33,438 --> 00:05:36,563
We'd sort of dated for 2 years, so...

46
00:05:36,563 --> 00:05:38,397
You married for that?

47
00:05:39,730 --> 00:05:43,064
Don't be picky or you'll miss your chance.

48
00:05:43,064 --> 00:05:48,522
Marriage isn't a must, you know.
You haven't changed.

49
00:05:48,522 --> 00:05:50,064
Look who's talking.

50
00:06:00,313 --> 00:06:02,647
I want to treat Chikako right.

51
00:06:05,814 --> 00:06:08,730
What I'm doing doesn't make sense.

52
00:06:10,522 --> 00:06:14,563
But how I feel about one and the other are so different.

53
00:06:17,397 --> 00:06:19,147
I was an idiot.

54
00:06:24,313 --> 00:06:27,897
You're a man, so you get it, don't you?

55
00:06:30,730 --> 00:06:33,730
Why do you want to treat her right?

56
00:06:36,104 --> 00:06:39,979
Because I love her. Why else?

57
00:06:40,895 --> 00:06:41,979
Do you really?

58
00:06:43,562 --> 00:06:45,395
Not just sort of?

59
00:06:48,478 --> 00:06:49,728
I do love her.

60
00:07:10,062 --> 00:07:11,728
I'll straighten things out,

61
00:07:14,187 --> 00:07:15,353
so please.

62
00:07:30,728 --> 00:07:32,979
Thank you for dinner.

63
00:07:36,645 --> 00:07:37,645
Hey.

64
00:07:41,145 --> 00:07:43,229
You won't tell Chikako, will you?

65
00:08:05,229 --> 00:08:07,562
You smell like cigarettes.

66
00:08:07,562 --> 00:08:09,478
You quit smoking?

67
00:08:09,478 --> 00:08:12,728
Yeah. Because Chikako doesn't like it.

68
00:08:16,895 --> 00:08:19,229
Hey, you said only kissing.

69
00:08:19,229 --> 00:08:21,520
Wouldn't want it to get wrinkled.

70
00:08:43,271 --> 00:08:44,271
Sorry.

71
00:08:46,895 --> 00:08:48,062
About what?

72
00:08:48,062 --> 00:08:49,562
I can't do this.

73
00:08:49,562 --> 00:08:51,478
All I asked for is kissing.

74
00:08:51,478 --> 00:08:54,145
Come on. It's not that easy.

75
00:08:57,229 --> 00:09:00,395
You're in love with me?

76
00:09:03,645 --> 00:09:04,979
Yes, I am.

77
00:09:17,062 --> 00:09:18,926
No tongue.

78
00:09:18,926 --> 00:09:20,759
You don't have a choice.

79
00:10:16,395 --> 00:10:17,395
Here.

80
00:10:20,728 --> 00:10:24,145
Hey, why don't we go out to eat this weekend?

81
00:10:25,395 --> 00:10:27,271
Any requests?

82
00:10:27,271 --> 00:10:28,395
Why?

83
00:10:29,229 --> 00:10:33,645
Well, I wanted to go see a movie for a change.

84
00:10:33,645 --> 00:10:35,812
And go shopping while we're at it.

85
00:10:39,502 --> 00:10:41,251
There's a movie I want to see.

86
00:10:41,251 --> 00:10:43,460
Oh, then let's see it.

87
00:10:43,460 --> 00:10:44,626
It's a horror film. You sure?

88
00:10:45,293 --> 00:10:46,460
What, a horror?

89
00:10:48,959 --> 00:10:50,043
Sure.

90
00:10:52,467 --> 00:10:56,217
I actually wanted to buy some clothes, too.

91
00:10:58,001 --> 00:10:59,709
Can't wait.

92
00:10:59,709 --> 00:11:01,293
Yeah, me too.

93
00:11:15,793 --> 00:11:17,168
Good evening.

94
00:11:17,168 --> 00:11:18,168
Hi.

95
00:11:19,210 --> 00:11:20,210
Come in.

96
00:12:24,001 --> 00:12:25,626
What are you doing?

97
00:12:26,829 --> 00:12:29,126
- Why?
- Did you break up with her?

98
00:12:32,751 --> 00:12:37,793
Your wife will find proof on her own
and accuse us of doing a sloppy job.

99
00:12:40,502 --> 00:12:42,126
Are you still tailing me?

100
00:12:42,126 --> 00:12:45,001
I told your wife that you weren't cheating.

101
00:12:45,001 --> 00:12:47,376
But she told me to keep investigating.

102
00:12:52,959 --> 00:12:54,876
I'll stop cheating.

103
00:12:54,876 --> 00:13:00,126
Then go back and tell her now.
Or you could text her from here.

104
00:13:00,126 --> 00:13:02,460
How could I do that?

105
00:13:02,460 --> 00:13:06,793
You're having an affair and will choose
your wife if it surfaces.

106
00:13:08,541 --> 00:13:12,208
It'll be cruel no matter how you break up with her.

107
00:13:16,667 --> 00:13:18,375
You're right, but she...

108
00:13:19,958 --> 00:13:21,041
I mean...

109
00:13:22,874 --> 00:13:26,708
She said she didn't mind.
She doesn't care if I'm married.

110
00:13:27,458 --> 00:13:30,791
How do you say no to something like that?

111
00:13:32,458 --> 00:13:36,958
That's all there is between us.
And I've only been here 3 times.

112
00:13:40,958 --> 00:13:42,291
I won't see her anymore.

113
00:13:43,791 --> 00:13:46,375
But how will she feel if I text her now?

114
00:13:48,500 --> 00:13:52,625
How you break up with people matters, you know.

115
00:13:59,999 --> 00:14:01,791
- I'm telling your wife.
- Why?

116
00:14:01,791 --> 00:14:05,958
Because it's my job, of course.

117
00:14:10,958 --> 00:14:12,208
Imagase!

118
00:14:51,708 --> 00:14:54,625
Hey, just kissing, right?

119
00:14:54,625 --> 00:14:56,375
I didn't say where.

120
00:15:07,583 --> 00:15:08,583
Hey.

121
00:15:47,458 --> 00:15:48,625
I'm home.

122
00:16:23,791 --> 00:16:24,958
I'm home.

123
00:16:25,958 --> 00:16:27,041
What's the matter?

124
00:16:28,667 --> 00:16:31,124
Nothing, just letting you know.

125
00:16:36,465 --> 00:16:37,674
I'd like a shower, too.

126
00:16:38,667 --> 00:16:40,874
OK, I'll be out in a sec.

127
00:16:56,355 --> 00:16:58,189
Mr. Otomo.

128
00:16:58,189 --> 00:17:03,606
I fixed the proposal based on yesterday's meeting.
Could you check it?

129
00:17:03,606 --> 00:17:04,939
Sure, let's see it.

130
00:17:12,272 --> 00:17:15,230
Ms. Okamura, want some coffee?

131
00:17:15,230 --> 00:17:16,439
Oh, shall I get some?

132
00:17:16,439 --> 00:17:18,939
Actually, I didn't sleep well last night.

133
00:17:19,898 --> 00:17:21,856
Want to join me?

134
00:17:22,564 --> 00:17:23,480
Sure.

135
00:17:23,480 --> 00:17:27,314
[Organize Requirements]

136
00:17:27,314 --> 00:17:29,063
[Solutions]

137
00:17:32,439 --> 00:17:33,522
Looks good.

138
00:17:36,063 --> 00:17:39,439
Thank you. I'll send it to our client, then.

139
00:17:39,439 --> 00:17:41,189
Yeah, please do.

140
00:17:48,606 --> 00:17:50,022
You really do seem sleepy.

141
00:17:52,856 --> 00:17:56,606
I've been having trouble falling asleep lately.

142
00:18:00,063 --> 00:18:03,522
How about you? What time do you go to bed?

143
00:18:04,606 --> 00:18:10,022
It's kind of embarrassing, but around 10 p.m.
if I'm not doing anything.

144
00:18:11,272 --> 00:18:13,022
That's pretty early.

145
00:18:14,856 --> 00:18:17,606
But it's probably better that way.

146
00:18:17,606 --> 00:18:19,022
Maybe so.

147
00:18:22,314 --> 00:18:25,105
[Please try this tea.]

148
00:18:43,689 --> 00:18:44,856
Thanks for waiting.

149
00:18:46,063 --> 00:18:47,105
This one.

150
00:18:47,105 --> 00:18:49,480
This one? OK.

151
00:18:49,480 --> 00:18:51,839
- Thanks.
- Sure.

152
00:18:51,839 --> 00:18:54,355
- I'll take this.
- Thank you.

153
00:18:54,355 --> 00:18:57,439
Here you go. Shiba shrimp in chili sauce.

154
00:18:58,355 --> 00:18:59,772
Enjoy.

155
00:19:08,439 --> 00:19:10,355
Thanks for today.

156
00:19:10,355 --> 00:19:11,522
No problem.

157
00:19:12,856 --> 00:19:17,689
Actually, sorry for not being
able to take you out lately.

158
00:19:21,564 --> 00:19:24,063
You're always so busy, Kyoichi.

159
00:19:26,022 --> 00:19:27,772
We should do some traveling.

160
00:19:40,147 --> 00:19:41,272
What's wrong?

161
00:19:54,397 --> 00:19:55,439
Sorry.

162
00:20:09,955 --> 00:20:11,288
Please...

163
00:20:15,955 --> 00:20:17,621
break up with me.

164
00:20:18,329 --> 00:20:19,329
What?

165
00:20:21,162 --> 00:20:23,788
Hold on, let's talk.

166
00:20:30,830 --> 00:20:32,538
You misunderstand.

167
00:20:32,538 --> 00:20:33,955
Misunderstand what?

168
00:20:42,454 --> 00:20:44,121
Sorry for being selfish.

169
00:20:46,878 --> 00:20:48,378
But I...

170
00:20:50,038 --> 00:20:55,705
hired a private detective to check
if you were cheating on me.

171
00:21:00,663 --> 00:21:02,038
You truly are...

172
00:21:04,454 --> 00:21:07,955
the perfect husband, aren't you?

173
00:21:09,121 --> 00:21:10,121
What?

174
00:21:12,329 --> 00:21:14,288
No sign of infidelity.

175
00:21:16,955 --> 00:21:18,788
If you'd been cheating,

176
00:21:21,198 --> 00:21:25,115
then I could have demanded a lot of compensation.

177
00:21:33,387 --> 00:21:35,887
I've been seeing someone else.

178
00:21:39,470 --> 00:21:41,220
It's been over a year.

179
00:21:45,096 --> 00:21:47,303
Didn't you notice?

180
00:21:52,595 --> 00:21:54,387
I trusted you.

181
00:21:54,387 --> 00:21:55,970
Trusted me?

182
00:22:01,762 --> 00:22:03,137
Our marriage...

183
00:22:04,929 --> 00:22:09,804
was just about you bringing me money
and me spending it.

184
00:22:12,303 --> 00:22:15,137
That's all there ever was between us.

185
00:22:17,220 --> 00:22:19,470
There was more than that.

186
00:22:29,220 --> 00:22:31,054
You always do that.

187
00:22:32,970 --> 00:22:36,553
That way you sit there waiting for me
to say something,

188
00:22:40,553 --> 00:22:42,137
is so repulsive.

189
00:22:52,870 --> 00:22:54,609
I want to break up...

190
00:22:56,786 --> 00:22:58,120
for his sake.

191
00:23:18,120 --> 00:23:19,120
Yes?

192
00:23:19,953 --> 00:23:21,619
Did you know?

193
00:23:22,369 --> 00:23:24,120
Know what?

194
00:23:24,120 --> 00:23:27,244
The reason why Chikako hired you.

195
00:23:27,244 --> 00:23:28,286
The reason?

196
00:23:31,744 --> 00:23:34,536
Sorry. I'll call you again.

197
00:23:35,870 --> 00:23:37,286
Did something happen?

198
00:23:39,036 --> 00:23:40,203
Never mind.

199
00:23:42,536 --> 00:23:45,619
Why would a client reveal something like that?

200
00:23:47,703 --> 00:23:48,786
You're right.

201
00:23:50,286 --> 00:23:52,120
Sorry, I'll call again.

202
00:23:52,786 --> 00:23:53,786
Wait.

203
00:23:55,744 --> 00:23:58,661
You called because something happened.

204
00:23:58,661 --> 00:24:00,286
I said, never mind.

205
00:24:00,286 --> 00:24:02,369
Did she ask for a divorce?

206
00:24:04,610 --> 00:24:06,953
None of your business.

207
00:24:06,953 --> 00:24:08,369
Are you separating?

208
00:24:11,786 --> 00:24:13,203
Yeah.

209
00:24:14,162 --> 00:24:15,162
I see.

210
00:24:16,078 --> 00:24:19,286
So you're getting a divorce.

211
00:24:19,286 --> 00:24:21,786
Then my investigation is really over.

212
00:24:23,302 --> 00:24:24,343
Who is that?

213
00:24:25,677 --> 00:24:30,302
Sorry, you're with someone. I'll hang up now.

214
00:24:32,094 --> 00:24:33,261
Take care.

215
00:24:40,426 --> 00:24:41,426
Who was that?

216
00:24:46,927 --> 00:24:49,385
Someone I've loved for a long time.

217
00:25:19,468 --> 00:25:20,635
Want to play rugby?

218
00:25:21,385 --> 00:25:25,219
You're a freshman, right? Join our tennis club!

219
00:25:26,843 --> 00:25:28,718
Want to join our club?

220
00:25:31,219 --> 00:25:36,552
I think the difficult aspects about women are cute, too.

221
00:25:36,552 --> 00:25:38,219
That's deep.

222
00:25:38,219 --> 00:25:40,885
Right. Their difficult sides are cute.

223
00:25:40,885 --> 00:25:42,760
How would you know?

224
00:25:42,760 --> 00:25:44,261
- Of course I know.
- No way!

225
00:26:34,217 --> 00:26:36,675
You knew where I moved?

226
00:26:36,675 --> 00:26:38,550
Here, a housewarming gift.

227
00:26:39,717 --> 00:26:41,300
After so long?

228
00:26:44,300 --> 00:26:45,342
Want to come in?

229
00:26:53,717 --> 00:26:56,883
You must be sick of living alone by now.

230
00:26:56,883 --> 00:27:01,134
Nah, I've been hanging loose. No one to fuss over.

231
00:27:01,134 --> 00:27:02,300
I see.

232
00:27:08,259 --> 00:27:09,883
So you can cook.

233
00:27:11,426 --> 00:27:15,217
What about you? How's it going with your boyfriend?

234
00:27:15,217 --> 00:27:16,217
What?

235
00:27:21,883 --> 00:27:23,883
We broke up long ago.

236
00:27:26,717 --> 00:27:28,384
Will you go out with me?

237
00:27:29,967 --> 00:27:32,426
Why would I go out with a guy?

238
00:27:32,426 --> 00:27:33,800
You're right.

239
00:27:35,717 --> 00:27:38,659
Then let's go out for drinks sometimes.

240
00:27:38,659 --> 00:27:42,993
And maybe go to a hot spring on a long weekend.

241
00:27:44,717 --> 00:27:46,326
A hot spring, huh?

242
00:27:47,633 --> 00:27:48,717
Sounds good.

243
00:27:55,175 --> 00:27:57,050
Don't.

244
00:27:57,050 --> 00:27:58,717
Come on, man.

245
00:29:47,550 --> 00:29:49,467
[Mr. Kyoichi Otomo]

246
00:29:58,967 --> 00:30:03,050
[Will Attend / Will Not Attend]

247
00:30:05,050 --> 00:30:08,467
[Alumni of 2007 Class Reunion]

248
00:30:21,217 --> 00:30:23,134
Don't come in.

249
00:30:27,058 --> 00:30:29,392
Are you going to your high school reunion?

250
00:30:31,800 --> 00:30:33,183
Why do you ask?

251
00:30:34,967 --> 00:30:39,883
Some girl you used to like will now be
a hot married woman,

252
00:30:39,883 --> 00:30:43,967
and she's going to make you an offer you can't refuse.

253
00:30:46,300 --> 00:30:47,800
What are you saying?

254
00:30:53,266 --> 00:30:55,015
Stop it. Hey.

255
00:31:01,015 --> 00:31:04,015
Stop! Don't, I'm serious!

256
00:31:07,182 --> 00:31:08,599
Let me sleep.

257
00:31:14,414 --> 00:31:18,516
You don't know when to give in, do you?

258
00:31:18,516 --> 00:31:20,432
I'm never giving in.

259
00:31:38,474 --> 00:31:40,516
I'm not going to the reunion.

260
00:31:51,573 --> 00:31:57,739
We've reevaluated the presentation
of the new product based on our meeting.

261
00:31:57,739 --> 00:32:00,448
Our creative director will explain.

262
00:32:01,781 --> 00:32:07,781
Please take a look at this video
and tell us what you think.

263
00:32:07,781 --> 00:32:09,573
- Play the video.
- Yes.

264
00:32:13,406 --> 00:32:17,198
Diane Bonheur has set standards for fair trade,

265
00:32:17,198 --> 00:32:21,365
traceability, and sustainability.
We've created this video

266
00:32:21,365 --> 00:32:26,698
to introduce this new product's appeal
to as many people as possible.

267
00:32:27,615 --> 00:32:29,989
This video will be shown at the event...

268
00:32:33,781 --> 00:32:34,948
Mr. Otomo!

269
00:32:38,615 --> 00:32:39,864
Long time no see.

270
00:32:43,080 --> 00:32:45,330
Is it true you got divorced?

271
00:32:46,497 --> 00:32:47,663
It's true.

272
00:32:51,580 --> 00:32:53,497
Was it my fault?

273
00:32:55,246 --> 00:32:56,580
No.

274
00:33:00,629 --> 00:33:01,796
I see.

275
00:33:04,504 --> 00:33:08,420
I know you cared a lot about your wife.

276
00:33:12,246 --> 00:33:15,163
Why did you stop replying to my texts?

277
00:33:16,745 --> 00:33:21,622
Sorry. I was busy moving out and stuff.

278
00:33:21,622 --> 00:33:24,163
You already live on your own?

279
00:33:24,163 --> 00:33:25,663
Yeah.

280
00:33:25,663 --> 00:33:27,996
Have you been eating right?

281
00:33:27,996 --> 00:33:31,413
Yeah. Why do you ask?

282
00:33:31,413 --> 00:33:34,246
Well, you seem to have lost weight.

283
00:33:34,246 --> 00:33:35,497
You think so?

284
00:33:36,288 --> 00:33:38,080
Yeah. You look different now.

285
00:33:43,913 --> 00:33:45,330
I have to go now.

286
00:33:47,121 --> 00:33:48,413
See you.

287
00:33:48,413 --> 00:33:49,497
See you.

288
00:33:52,913 --> 00:33:55,747
Yes? Sorry, I'll be right there.

289
00:34:06,004 --> 00:34:07,130
Kiss me.

290
00:34:07,130 --> 00:34:09,007
Leave me alone.

291
00:34:09,007 --> 00:34:10,090
Meanie.

292
00:34:22,045 --> 00:34:23,212
You're heavy.

293
00:34:23,212 --> 00:34:25,378
- Clean my ears.
- No way.

294
00:34:26,879 --> 00:34:28,295
I'll clean yours.

295
00:34:31,076 --> 00:34:32,076
Really?

296
00:34:33,887 --> 00:34:35,470
I'm good at it.

297
00:34:37,962 --> 00:34:40,285
OK, then.

298
00:34:45,045 --> 00:34:46,295
It's a bit dark.

299
00:35:07,545 --> 00:35:08,545
Yes?

300
00:35:09,545 --> 00:35:11,295
Are you home?

301
00:35:11,295 --> 00:35:13,545
Yeah, almost home.

302
00:35:17,086 --> 00:35:19,378
Sorry for suddenly calling.

303
00:35:19,378 --> 00:35:21,629
It's OK. What's up?

304
00:35:25,921 --> 00:35:30,045
When we spoke the other day at your company,

305
00:35:30,045 --> 00:35:33,629
it felt like our conversation ended awkwardly.

306
00:35:34,879 --> 00:35:37,462
We'll be meeting on business again soon.

307
00:35:38,921 --> 00:35:42,879
I wanted to make sure things were OK before then.

308
00:35:53,511 --> 00:35:55,220
I missed you.

309
00:35:59,045 --> 00:36:02,295
Are you not interested in me anymore?

310
00:36:52,754 --> 00:36:54,295
Sorry I'm home so late.

311
00:36:56,378 --> 00:36:58,045
You ate dinner, right?

312
00:36:58,045 --> 00:36:59,295
Yeah, I did.

313
00:37:08,378 --> 00:37:09,837
What was for dinner tonight?

314
00:37:09,837 --> 00:37:11,462
Macaroni casserole.

315
00:37:11,462 --> 00:37:12,962
Maybe I'll have some.

316
00:37:14,378 --> 00:37:17,962
So greedy. Eat it tomorrow, you'll gain weight.

317
00:37:19,754 --> 00:37:24,128
You're right. Sorry, I'll have some tomorrow.

318
00:37:26,045 --> 00:37:27,128
How about a bath?

319
00:37:28,212 --> 00:37:30,045
Oh, is it ready?

320
00:37:30,045 --> 00:37:32,045
I just heated it up.

321
00:37:33,003 --> 00:37:34,128
I'll go in, then.

322
00:38:32,544 --> 00:38:33,795
Stop that!

323
00:38:33,795 --> 00:38:36,712
You're still seeing that woman.

324
00:38:36,712 --> 00:38:39,295
You said you weren't that into her.

325
00:38:41,493 --> 00:38:46,743
I met her again at work. She wanted to see me
and I couldn't say no.

326
00:38:46,743 --> 00:38:48,910
Never can say no, huh?

327
00:38:51,079 --> 00:38:53,201
You're so easy.

328
00:38:53,201 --> 00:38:57,921
I'm not going out with you or anything, you know.

329
00:38:57,921 --> 00:39:01,921
I know. But then why did you lie about having to work?

330
00:39:05,077 --> 00:39:08,660
I apologize for lying to you.

331
00:39:14,077 --> 00:39:18,243
I thought you might not like it if I told you the truth.

332
00:39:26,410 --> 00:39:32,243
I'm really not the kind of guy
you should care so much about.

333
00:39:33,326 --> 00:39:35,576
You think I don't know that?

334
00:39:36,952 --> 00:39:39,326
People like you are the worst.

335
00:39:43,517 --> 00:39:47,684
But do you think everyone is looking for good-looking,

336
00:39:47,684 --> 00:39:52,143
