337
00:39:56,309 --> 00:39:58,392
That's not how it works.

338
00:40:02,559 --> 00:40:03,642
Imagase!

339
00:40:06,018 --> 00:40:07,018
Hey!

340
00:40:57,601 --> 00:41:00,809
[Kyoichi Otomo]

341
00:41:14,392 --> 00:41:15,476
What's up?

342
00:41:18,559 --> 00:41:20,226
You still angry?

343
00:41:25,851 --> 00:41:27,726
Why are you calling me?

344
00:41:30,642 --> 00:41:33,976
Right. I'll hang up, then.

345
00:41:35,226 --> 00:41:38,809
I've been busy working lately,

346
00:41:38,809 --> 00:41:43,226
looking for a missing person in Kyushu and Shikoku.

347
00:41:44,976 --> 00:41:46,268
Where are you now?

348
00:41:47,767 --> 00:41:48,893
At home.

349
00:41:50,575 --> 00:41:51,575
Alone?

350
00:41:52,284 --> 00:41:53,284
Yes.

351
00:41:55,908 --> 00:41:57,449
Want to come out to eat?

352
00:42:00,350 --> 00:42:01,474
Now?

353
00:42:21,807 --> 00:42:24,391
What have you been up to this past week?

354
00:42:26,350 --> 00:42:27,974
Nothing. The usual.

355
00:42:29,224 --> 00:42:31,391
So, what do you want?

356
00:42:32,308 --> 00:42:36,724
Got hungry at this hour
but calling a woman was too much trouble?

357
00:42:38,474 --> 00:42:41,224
What about you? Why did you come?

358
00:42:42,308 --> 00:42:46,308
I'm the kind of guy who rushes over
when someone he loves calls.

359
00:42:55,391 --> 00:42:58,391
Was the missing person a man or a woman?

360
00:43:01,224 --> 00:43:05,266
A woman. Why do you ask?

361
00:43:05,266 --> 00:43:06,557
Did you find her?

362
00:43:09,432 --> 00:43:10,974
She was dead.

363
00:43:26,308 --> 00:43:27,766
What, aren't you coming in?

364
00:43:27,766 --> 00:43:29,099
Am I allowed in?

365
00:43:29,099 --> 00:43:30,641
Yeah, of course.

366
00:43:31,974 --> 00:43:33,724
Will you have sex with me?

367
00:43:36,724 --> 00:43:38,391
Just come on in.

368
00:45:00,307 --> 00:45:01,866
Here.

369
00:45:01,866 --> 00:45:03,682
No?

370
00:45:03,682 --> 00:45:04,724
Why?

371
00:45:10,599 --> 00:45:12,724
- How can you tell?
- I just can.

372
00:45:13,974 --> 00:45:15,188
I'll get it this time.

373
00:45:15,974 --> 00:45:16,974
Here.

374
00:45:20,099 --> 00:45:21,641
I can tell from behind, too.

375
00:45:23,557 --> 00:45:25,308
Hold on.

376
00:45:25,308 --> 00:45:27,224
What are you doing?

377
00:45:29,515 --> 00:45:33,474
Whoa, whoa, stop. I can't stand this.

378
00:45:45,724 --> 00:45:48,141
Don't you have a new girlfriend?

379
00:45:48,141 --> 00:45:49,557
Nope.

380
00:45:49,557 --> 00:45:51,474
What? Really?

381
00:45:51,474 --> 00:45:52,682
What about you?

382
00:45:52,682 --> 00:45:55,141
Nobody at all.

383
00:45:55,141 --> 00:45:56,807
Introduce me to someone.

384
00:45:56,807 --> 00:45:57,807
Kyoichi?

385
00:46:00,981 --> 00:46:01,981
Natsuki?

386
00:46:03,315 --> 00:46:06,106
- Wow, it's been so long.
- Long time no see.

387
00:46:07,356 --> 00:46:10,398
It's so like you to be divorced.

388
00:46:12,106 --> 00:46:14,814
Did the easy samurai cheat a lot?

389
00:46:14,814 --> 00:46:16,273
Easy samurai?

390
00:46:16,273 --> 00:46:18,064
Brings back memories, huh?

391
00:46:18,064 --> 00:46:20,356
Yeah, it does.

392
00:46:22,523 --> 00:46:27,273
Do you still see anyone from back then?
I went to Asami's wedding.

393
00:46:27,273 --> 00:46:29,523
Oh, Asami got married?

394
00:46:30,398 --> 00:46:33,856
I drink with Yoshikawa and Tsuchida sometimes.

395
00:46:33,856 --> 00:46:35,814
Oh, let me join you.

396
00:46:35,814 --> 00:46:38,315
OK, I'll let you know next time.

397
00:46:38,315 --> 00:46:40,606
Hey? Natsuki?

398
00:46:42,773 --> 00:46:46,064
Imagase! It's been so long! How are you?

399
00:46:46,064 --> 00:46:47,190
Long time no see.

400
00:46:48,440 --> 00:46:49,523
Mr. Otomo.

401
00:46:52,489 --> 00:46:53,780
Long time no see.

402
00:46:54,814 --> 00:46:56,190
Yeah, hi.

403
00:46:56,190 --> 00:46:58,482
May we join you? I'm with a friend.

404
00:46:58,482 --> 00:46:59,523
Sure, of course.

405
00:47:00,693 --> 00:47:06,939
Hello, I'm Takasugi. I've been friends
with Imagase for a long time.

406
00:47:06,939 --> 00:47:08,606
Sorry for intruding.

407
00:47:08,606 --> 00:47:09,689
No problem.

408
00:47:11,355 --> 00:47:12,521
You just got here?

409
00:47:12,521 --> 00:47:13,729
Yes.

410
00:47:13,729 --> 00:47:15,355
What will you drink?

411
00:47:15,355 --> 00:47:17,313
So you're Mr. Otomo.

412
00:47:19,404 --> 00:47:22,529
I've heard a lot about you.

413
00:47:25,605 --> 00:47:28,522
Are you still going out with Mr. Otomo?

414
00:47:28,522 --> 00:47:32,439
No way! We happened to run into each other recently.

415
00:47:34,104 --> 00:47:36,104
You're still as pretty as ever.

416
00:47:37,021 --> 00:47:39,313
Oh, stop that. I've changed a lot.

417
00:47:39,313 --> 00:47:41,647
Not at all. Are you married?

418
00:47:41,647 --> 00:47:43,355
Nope. No prospects, either.

419
00:47:43,355 --> 00:47:44,521
I see.

420
00:47:45,771 --> 00:47:46,912
What about you?

421
00:47:48,188 --> 00:47:50,021
I'm...

422
00:47:52,188 --> 00:47:54,771
trying to make someone I adore love me back.

423
00:47:56,771 --> 00:47:59,021
What's this person like?

424
00:47:59,021 --> 00:48:01,021
- May I smoke?
- Go ahead.

425
00:49:18,827 --> 00:49:21,203
You unlocked my phone again, didn't you?

426
00:49:24,812 --> 00:49:26,521
You went through my texts.

427
00:49:28,261 --> 00:49:31,052
Why are you seeing Natsuki again?

428
00:49:31,052 --> 00:49:32,681
And you? What's with him?

429
00:49:32,681 --> 00:49:35,722
I hadn't seen him in a while and he called, so.

430
00:49:36,761 --> 00:49:38,969
You're a better match with him.

431
00:49:50,052 --> 00:49:51,052
Stop it!

432
00:49:53,969 --> 00:49:56,719
I don't care who you see or what you do.

433
00:49:59,124 --> 00:50:04,624
But I did feel that you and he are pals
who belong in a different world.

434
00:50:13,010 --> 00:50:16,969
Sorry. That was harsh.

435
00:50:48,219 --> 00:50:51,511
Imagase and his friend had things to do and left.

436
00:50:51,511 --> 00:50:53,386
Oh.

437
00:50:53,386 --> 00:50:55,052
They said it was nice meeting you.

438
00:50:59,393 --> 00:51:02,017
Imagase has become even more attractive.

439
00:51:04,177 --> 00:51:06,136
Yeah, I guess.

440
00:51:09,969 --> 00:51:14,886
You know what? I think
he was in love with you back then.

441
00:51:14,886 --> 00:51:17,469
Huh? Why?

442
00:51:17,469 --> 00:51:21,010
I always noticed him looking this way.

443
00:51:22,219 --> 00:51:25,302
I thought maybe he was in love with me,

444
00:51:26,636 --> 00:51:29,010
but that lighter gave it away.

445
00:51:29,010 --> 00:51:30,761
Lighter?

446
00:51:30,761 --> 00:51:35,953
Remember we argued because you were
using a lighter you got from an ex?

447
00:51:36,678 --> 00:51:38,010
No, did we?

448
00:51:38,010 --> 00:51:42,553
A pink Zippo. It had gift from a woman
written all over it.

449
00:51:43,636 --> 00:51:45,803
You don't remember?

450
00:51:46,577 --> 00:51:50,076
You gave it to Imagase because he said he wanted it.

451
00:51:51,660 --> 00:51:53,202
He's still using it.

452
00:51:56,035 --> 00:51:59,035
Oh. Guess he hangs on to stuff.

453
00:52:07,118 --> 00:52:08,118
Thank you.

454
00:52:09,452 --> 00:52:10,535
See you.

455
00:52:11,952 --> 00:52:13,577
I'll get off here too.

456
00:52:13,577 --> 00:52:15,619
It's OK, I'll be fine.

457
00:52:17,869 --> 00:52:19,869
- Here's your change.
- Thank you.

458
00:52:22,535 --> 00:52:25,869
See, you're not OK.

459
00:52:28,827 --> 00:52:31,035
- Natsuki.
- What?

460
00:52:31,035 --> 00:52:32,452
Long time no see.

461
00:52:32,452 --> 00:52:36,535
Yeah, yeah. Come on, where's your key?

462
00:52:42,285 --> 00:52:45,118
Why did you drink so much?

463
00:52:45,118 --> 00:52:46,285
Hey?

464
00:52:46,285 --> 00:52:47,535
Where?

465
00:52:47,535 --> 00:52:50,368
- My bag.
- Where in your bag?

466
00:52:50,368 --> 00:52:51,368
I don't know.

467
00:52:51,368 --> 00:52:55,785
Come on, look for it. It's in your bag, right?

468
00:52:55,785 --> 00:52:56,952
Welcome back.

469
00:52:59,744 --> 00:53:03,452
Oh, you're home.

470
00:53:03,452 --> 00:53:07,452
I thought you took off somewhere with that guy.

471
00:53:08,535 --> 00:53:11,535
You're so drunk. Are you all right?

472
00:53:11,535 --> 00:53:13,202
Up you go.

473
00:53:19,035 --> 00:53:23,202
Thank you for bringing him home.
Won't you come in?

474
00:53:24,702 --> 00:53:27,869
No... It's kind of late...

475
00:53:27,869 --> 00:53:30,118
Good night, then.

476
00:54:18,608 --> 00:54:20,150
Back in university,

477
00:54:22,483 --> 00:54:25,983
I thought you disliked me to be honest.

478
00:54:53,566 --> 00:54:55,400
Is this biting?

479
00:54:55,400 --> 00:54:56,566
Can I pull it out?

480
00:55:01,858 --> 00:55:03,566
We really got one!

481
00:55:03,566 --> 00:55:05,608
- No way!
- There are really fish in here.

482
00:55:13,431 --> 00:55:14,431
Hello?

483
00:55:21,775 --> 00:55:26,150
Got it. Yeah. See you.

484
00:55:28,441 --> 00:55:29,733
Natsuki?

485
00:55:29,733 --> 00:55:32,983
Yeah. I'm seeing her tonight.

486
00:55:34,400 --> 00:55:35,400
Oh.

487
00:55:39,316 --> 00:55:40,483
You OK with it?

488
00:55:41,817 --> 00:55:42,983
Go ahead.

489
00:55:55,316 --> 00:55:58,191
- Finally, you're here.
- Sorry.

490
00:55:58,191 --> 00:55:59,650
Have you decided what to eat?

491
00:55:59,650 --> 00:56:02,876
- You made no reservation?
- No, I asked you to decide.

492
00:56:31,858 --> 00:56:33,067
I'm home.

493
00:56:48,900 --> 00:56:50,316
You're home early.

494
00:56:51,109 --> 00:56:53,067
Yeah, I guess.

495
00:56:56,900 --> 00:56:59,983
Hey, where's my room wear?

496
00:57:06,025 --> 00:57:07,233
You perv.

497
00:57:07,233 --> 00:57:09,316
You're not drunk today.

498
00:57:10,606 --> 00:57:11,731
What's your point?

499
00:57:11,731 --> 00:57:13,982
What did Natsuki want?

500
00:57:13,982 --> 00:57:15,731
Nothing.

501
00:57:15,731 --> 00:57:16,898
Oh.

502
00:57:29,940 --> 00:57:31,898
I'm going for a walk.

503
00:57:33,898 --> 00:57:34,940
Be back soon.

504
00:59:01,789 --> 00:59:03,497
I'm so scared.

505
00:59:04,413 --> 00:59:08,373
